text:
272-8 Bleecker Street, at the N.W. corner of Morton Street, as viewed southwestward from Jones Street. Mr. Sperr reports the following:

"Doorway opposite Jones Street stairs led to meeting rooms much used for political gatherings. Theodore Roosevelt spoke here when a candidate for Mayor."

1899

J. J. Corell
P. L. Sperr

262-270 Bleecker Street, adjoining and at the S.E. corner of Morton (originally Ardens) Street. May 1, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH
